The paper introduces a new framework for graph neural networks (GNNs) that extends them to continuous time. This makes it likely that the paper would be categorized under machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper evaluates the effectiveness of the proposed framework on both static and dynamic datasets, which suggests that it could also be categorized under neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) or social and information networks (cs.SI).
